Basic Keylogger (Keystroke Logger for Educational Use)
🛡️ Overview
This is a simple keylogger tool built in Python for educational and ethical use only. It captures and logs all keyboard inputs made on the system and saves them to a text file.

⚠️ Ethical Warning
🔐 This tool must only be used on machines you own or have explicit permission to monitor. Unauthorized use of keyloggers is illegal and unethical.

🚀 Features
Records all keystrokes (including special keys like space, enter, etc.).

Saves logged data to a local file (keylog.txt).

Terminates safely when ESC key is pressed.

🛠 Requirements
Python 3.x

pynput library

Install with:
pip install pynput

📦 How to Use
Run the script:
python keylogger.py

The script will:

Start listening to keyboard input

Save everything to keylog.txt

Stop and exit when you press the ESC key

📝 Output
Example contents of keylog.txt:
h e l l o   w o r l d [Enter] [Shift] H e l l o !

Regular characters are logged directly.

Special keys are noted in brackets ([Enter], [Backspace], etc.).

🔐 Security & Limitations
Not obfuscated or hidden — visible in the task manager.

For demonstration and practice purposes only.

Does not support stealth or persistence (not designed for malicious use).